                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hardy</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-02-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 28, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 27.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 43 of the 13th instant relative to the
                    application of Helena Pecare for a passport has been received.</p>
                <p>Under the circumstances detailed in the dispatch your refusal to grant the
                    passport to Miss Pecare has the Department’s approval.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
